author: Elizabeth Adetula For Metro.Co.Uk
title: Will Ronnie and Roxy from EastEnders be joining Strictly Come Dancing? | Metro News
text:
Elizabeth Adetula for Metro.co.uk Wednesday 15 Feb 2017 2:21 pm Roxy and Ronnie died at Ronnie’s wedding (Picture: Jack Barnes) 
Roxy and Ronnie are rumoured to be reuniting again on TV, this time on Strictly Come Dancing. Sponsored 13 realities of going wedding dress shopping 
The sisters made a dramatic exit off EastEnders on New Years Day after they both tragically drowned on Ronnie’s wedding day. 
According to The Sun , both Rita Simons and Samantha Womack (who play Ronnie and Roxy) are said to be on the ‘wishlist’ for Strictly bosses for the 15th series of the show airing this September. Both Ronnie and Roxy joined the show in 2007 (Picture: BBC) 
Strictly insiders told the publication: ‘It’s fair to say that people are keen to sign at least one of them and if at all possible both of the girls for the new series. 
‘Obviously it’s early days and lists are still being drawn up for potential candidates as there are all kinds of commitments that people have for the coming months.’
